<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1955-08-05T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1955-08-05T00:00:00-05:00" n="33" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d33">
                        <head>33. Telegram 389 to Geneva<note n="1" type="source" xml:id="d33fn1">Source: Department of State, Central Files, 611.93/8–555. Official
                                Use Only; Priority. Drafted by <persName corresp="#p_MWP_1">McConaughy</persName>. The time of transmission is
                                illegible.</note></head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right"><placeName>Washington</placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1955-08-05">August 5,
                                1955</date></dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <pb facs="d33-1" n="1" type="facsimile" xml:id="d33-1"/>
                        <p>389. For <persName corresp="#p_JUA_1">Johnson</persName>.</p>
                        <p>Do you have text June 3 statement Immigration Commissioner J.M. Swing? If
                            not we will telegraph text since it may be of use at next meeting.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_DJF_1"><hi rend="strong">Dulles</hi></persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>